  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This lack of expressivity can lead to these models underfitting the training data, resulting in suboptimal performance, particularly when confronted with complex relationships within graph data (Xu et al. 2018).",
    "Additionally, the presence of heterophily, where interconnected nodes exhibit diverse attributes or labels, presents a challenge for GNNs (Luan et al. 2022).",
    "GNNs may face difficulties when applied to heterophilic graphs in the context of link prediction (Zhou et al. 2022).",
    "An example of a heterophilic graph in drug synergy prediction is one that incorporates links representing synergistic interactions between drug pairs and various cell lines.",
    "Such a graph poses a challenge for link prediction, demanding for the adoption or development of GNNs specially tailored to operate on graphs with diverse node types and attributes such as Heterogeneous Graph Attention Networks (Wang et al. 2019)."
  ],
